<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-27T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/6–2744: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-27T23:00:00-04:00">June
                                        27, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5065. Please inform the Foreign Office that we should appreciate
                                being informed as soon as possible whether the appropriate British
                                    <pb facs="0723" n="711" xml:id="pg_711"/> authorities concur in
                                the joint goods subsidy program for Saudi Arabia worked out in Cairo
                                by Mr. Landis and British representatives there, who are understood
                                to have referred their suggested program to London for
                                    approval.<note n="16" xml:id="d778fn16">In his telegram 5271,
                                    July 4, 6 p.m., the Ambassador in the United Kingdom reported
                                    that he had been informed by the British Foreign Office that
                                    “the British Embassy in Washington has been instructed to inform
                                    the Department of the British Government’s reaction to the joint
                                    goods subsidy program for Saudi Arabia.” (890F.24/7–444)</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>